title: Grain mostly lower, livestock mostly higher
text:
Thu, Sep 3, 2015, 6:04 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 3 hrs 56 mins Grain mostly lower, livestock mostly higher Wheat, oats mixed, corn, soybeans lower, on the CBOT; beef mixed, pork higher on the CME. Associated Press – 32 minutes ago Recommend Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were mostly lower Wednesday on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for December delivery was off 7.25 cents to $4.79 a bushel; December corn fell 1.25 cents to 3.6750 a bushel; December oats were up .50 cent to 2.2450 a bushel; while November soybeans were unchanged at $8.74 a bushel. 
Beef was mixed and pork higher on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. October live cattle was off .10 cent to $1.4122 a pound; October feeder cattle gained .98 cent to $1.9630 a pound; while October lean hogs rose 1.80 cents to $.6977 a pound. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Retail spending to stay solid AAP 
New retail spending figures are expected to show a third straight month of stronger activity at the cash register. … Terms
